> 1 MB of data, wow!!  I don't think anyone will create a scenario with
> half as many objects as that scenario has.  Glad to know that scenario
> has a purpose [testing converters to handle large amounts of data)
> besides boosting up a team with lots of money.
>
> BTW, why play around with that scenario?  Is it because it has so many
> virtually identical objects?

Well a lot of the initial bugs in my code were caused on things like the
40th object or something else far down the list, so any other bugs should
show up if it's processing lots of data, well at least I hope they would :)
I wouldn't want to actually count the number of objects in the text file to
make sure they are all there though, for that I used one of them with 4
objects, much easier to count.

Anyway now you can feed it whatever scenario you want, if you find any
problems in it let me know!

- Deathifier
